                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12644569" author="jimk" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2008 07:45:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because the HTableDescriptor can be modified by both HBaseAdmin.modifyColumn and HBaseAdmin.modifyTable, fixing this on the master side would require code duplication and checks in some very awkward places. If the HTableDescriptor were readily accessible from the client, (such as being stored in Zookeeper for example), the client could prevent changing the bloomfilter setting before even sending a request to the master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12644570" author="jimk" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2008 07:48:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 0.20.0 since the best way of resolving this problem is if the HTableDescriptor is readily available to the client (which means moving HTableDescriptor out of HRegionInfo).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add a release note about this problem for 0.19.0, saying that a column&apos;s bloom filter setting should not be changed after the table is created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12701636" author="stack" created="Wed, 22 Apr 2009 18:55:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue became invalid when we moved to hfile.  We still need to deal with users enabling/disabling bloom filters but the game has changed where this issue is concerned.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
